  "prompt": "The current year is 2014. Why is this the 21st century and not the 20th century?",
  "response": "Great question! Understanding why the year 2014 is part of the **21st century** (and not the 20th) involves a bit of history about how we count centuries. Here's a clear explanation:\n\n### **How Centuries Are Numbered**\n\n1. **Starting Point:** The Gregorian calendar, which is widely used today, begins with **year 1 AD**. There is **no \"year 0\"** in this system.\n\n2. **Defining a Century:** \n   - **1st Century:** Years **1** through **100**.\n   - **2nd Century:** Years **101** through **200**.\n   - This pattern continues incrementally.\n\n3. **Applying to the 21st Century:**\n   - **20th Century:** Years **1901** through **2000**.\n   - **21st Century:** Years **2001** through **2100**.\n\n### **Common Misconception**\n\n- **Year 2000:** It might seem intuitive to consider the year **2000** as part of the **21st century** because it marks the start of a new millennium. However, according to the strict century-counting method:\n  - **Year 2000** is actually the **final year of the 20th century**.\n  - **Year 2001** officially begins the **21st century**.\n\n### **Why This System?**\n\n- Since there is no year 0, every new century starts with a year ending in **01** and ends with **00** of the new multiple of 100. This ensures that:\n  - Each century spans exactly **100 years**.\n  - The first century correctly starts with year 1.\n\n### **Implications for Today (2014)**\n\n- Given that **2014** falls between **2001** and **2100**, it is indeed part of the **21st century**.\n\n### **Visual Overview**\n\n| Century       | Years            |\n|---------------|------------------|\n| 1st Century   | 1 - 100          |\n| 20th Century  | 1901 - 2000      |\n| 21st Century  | 2001 - 2100      |\n\n### **Summary**\n\n- **2014** is in the **21st century** because centuries are counted starting from year **1**, making **2001-2100** the span of the 21st century.\n- The **20th century** concluded with the year **2000**.\n\nI hope this clarifies why 2014 belongs to the 21st century!",
